description: From Middle English.  See etymology of the corresponding sense of strut.

verbs.description: strout (third-person singular simple present strouts, present participle strouting, simple past and past participle strouted)

entries.meaning: (obsolete, transitive) To cause to project or swell out; to enlarge affectedly; to strut.
(obsolete, intransitive) Alternative form of strut (“to swell; protuberate; bulge or spread out”)
examples: The daintie Clover growes (of grasse the onely silke)
That makes each Udder strout abundantly with milke.
